      <!-- FAQ Item -->
      <details class="group border-b border-gray-700 pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer text-lg font-medium list-none">
          Can a foreign investor own 100% of a Saudi company?
          <span class="transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="size-6">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="m4.5 15.75 7.5-7.5 7.5 7.5" />
            </svg>

          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 !text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          Yes — in most sectors. Saudi Arabia opened the majority of commercial activities to full foreign ownership under Vision 2030 reforms. MISA's approved activities list governs eligibility by sector. Some activities still require a Saudi partner; we assess your specific activity at the outset.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-b border-gray-700 pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer text-lg font-medium list-none">
          What is the minimum share capital required?
          <span class="transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="size-6">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="m4.5 15.75 7.5-7.5 7.5 7.5" />
            </svg>

          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 !text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          It varies by activity and entity type. For a standard foreign-owned LLC in commercial or consulting activities, the threshold can start from SAR 100,000, though MISA applies different requirements for industrial, healthcare, or financial services activities. We confirm the applicable figure after reviewing your activity list.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-b border-gray-700 pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer text-lg font-medium list-none">
          Do I need to be physically present in Saudi Arabia to register?
          <span class="transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="size-6">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="m4.5 15.75 7.5-7.5 7.5 7.5" />
            </svg>

          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 !text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          Not necessarily. Many steps can be managed remotely through a legal representative holding a duly authorised Power of Attorney. We advise on any steps that require your in-person presence and help plan accordingly.
        </p>
      </details>

       <details class="group border-b border-gray-700 pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer text-lg font-medium list-none">
          What taxes will my company be subject to?
          <span class="transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180">
